# Blog + SEO/AEO pipeline (mandatory)

This rule applies when **matched files are in context** (see `globs`). If you are planning blog ship work **without** those paths attached (chat-only), treat the user referring to **blog, post, article, publish, posts.ts, blog FAQ, or article schema** as the same obligation: **read `.cursor/skills/stratezik-blog-seo-pipeline/SKILL.md`** or ask them to **`@stratezik-blog-seo-pipeline`** once so context is explicit.

## MUST use all three skill files (do not skip)

For **any** Stratezik blog publish or overhaul (new post, rewrite, `posts.ts`, FAQ entities, article TSX):

1. **Read and follow** `.cursor/skills/stratezik-blog-seo-pipeline/SKILL.md` (**Chain A** or **Chain B**).
2. **Read and apply** `.cursor/skills/stratezik-seo-aeo/SKILL.md` for every SEO/AEO step that chain assigns (including **§8** for supplied drafts). Do not invent SEO checklist from memory when those steps apply.
3. **Read and apply** `.cursor/skills/stratezik-blog-writing/SKILL.md` for every draft, merge, or voice pass that chain assigns.

Skip (2) or (3) **only** if the user **explicitly** narrows scope (example: “rename variable only”, “fix one typo”).

4. Keep **`public/sitemap.xml`** and **`posts.ts`** aligned when URLs or dates change.
5. **Author/contact in article TSX:** `<BlogAuthorSignoff />` and `<BlogStratezikContactLink>` only — never hardcode names or `mailto:`. `npm run build` enforces via `scripts/check-blog-author.ts`.

**Default:** the user should not need to `@` skills for routine blog ship work when this rule is active; **you** open those three `SKILL.md` files at task start.
